              "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">Substance dependence, treated and stabilised</div>"
            },
            "code": {
              "coding": [
                {
                  "system": "http://loinc.org",
                  "code": "67781-5",
                  "display": "Summarization of encounter note"
                }
              ]
            },
            "title": "Synthesis"
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "status": "generated",
              "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">Dear colleague, thank you for referring this 46-year-old female patient, admitted on 02.01.2020 due to substance dependence disorder. Upon admission, a comprehensive psychiatric and somatic assessment was performed, confirming dependence on multiple substances including opioids and benzodiazepines. Withdrawal symptoms were present and required immediate clinical management. During her inpatient stay, a structured detoxification protocol was initiated, including pharmacological withdrawal treatment and close monitoring of vital signs and neurological status. Motivational counselling sessions were conducted, and a psychosocial needs assessment was completed. The patient stabilised well without major complications. At discharge on 05.01.2020, she was referred to an outpatient addiction support programme and her primary care follow-up was arranged. We recommend continued monitoring and engagement with community addiction services. Please do not hesitate to contact us should further information be required.</div>"
            },
